cs.HC, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on affective computing and emotion recognition, which are important topics in HCI research.
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also likely as the paper deals with natural language narratives and their emotional content.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the dataset includes videos of emotional narratives, and computer vision techniques are used to extract features from the videos.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses various machine learning models for time-series emotion recognition.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is relevant as the dataset includes multimodal videos with both visual and audio components.
